'''flannelette'''
#A type of [[soft]], [[woven]] [[fabric]], made to imitate [[flannel]] by raising or brushing the fibers in the [[weft]].  Frequently used in [[sleepwear]], [[pillows]], and [[bedding]].
#* 1954 "I am a [[draper]] mad with love. I love you more that all the '''flannelette''' and [[calico]], [[candlewick]], [[dimity]], [[crash]] and [[merino]], [[tussore]], [[cretonne]], [[crepon]], [[muslin]], [[poplin]], [[ticking]] and [[twill]] in the whole Cloth Hall of the world." ''Dylan Thomas: Under Milkwood. p.6.''
